comments: Morris (MIN) moves over the pick and initiates body contact with Murray (DEN), affecting his SQBR.
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in Morris's (MIN) path and is firming up when marginal contact occurs to Morris's side.
Murray (DEN) grabs Conley's (MIN) arm at the start of his drive and the contact affects his SQBR.
Conley (MIN) and Jokic (DEN) briefly engage and disengage.
Jokic (DEN) reaches across Conley (MIN) and initiates body contact that affects Conley's SQBR.
Conley (MIN) firms up in his defensive position to brace for the ensuing contact with Jokic (DEN) during his driving shot attempt.
Anderson (MIN) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Anderson (MIN) brings his hands toward Murray (DEN) and marginal contact occurs as Anderson releases away to roll.
Conley (MIN) reaches in and makes contact with the ball and marginal contact with Caldwell-Pope's (DEN) arm.
Jokic (DEN) has a hand placed over Anderson's (MIN) right arm during the rebound, but he quickly disengages.
McDaniels (MIN) jumps towards Porter Jr. (DEN) and initiates contact with Porter Jr.'s arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
The game is stopped due to a shot clock malfunction and play resumes with DEN retaining possession.
Conley (MIN) commits a take foul on Jokic (DEN).
Murray (DEN) briefly places his hand to Conley's (MIN) chest and immediately removes it prior to the start of his upward shooting motion.

Alexander-Walker (MIN) extends his arm forward to defend the pass and contact occurs to Caldwell-Pope's (DEN) face. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Conley (MIN) commits a take foul on Porter Jr. (DEN).
Anderson (MIN) inbounds the ball within 5 seconds.
McDaniels (MIN) commits a take foul on Murray (DEN).
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) is not established in Edwards' (MIN) path in transition when body contact occurs, but the contact does not affect Edwards' SQBR.
